arage door opener from the door using the red pull cord.";i:41;s:66:"If the door is working properly it should be easy to lift by hand.";i:42;s:98:"Clean lubricate adjust or call a garage door mechanic as apprpriate to the issues and your skills.";i:43;s:295:"Then go though the complete adjustment procedure for your opener including the safety tests that are supposed to be run every 6 months or so stops when beam broken stops and reverses when hitting a 2x4 laid flat on the floor closes and stops correctly when nothing is in the way opens correctly.";i:44;s:22:"Rusty or Jammed Parts.";i:45;s:105:"The rollers that slide your door up and down are more crucial to its proper operation than you may think.";i:46;s:50:"Be sure to clean and greaseoil these occasionally.";i:47;s:51:"The springs may be also be the source of the issue.";i:48;s:65:"If they arent lubricated properly they could stick or even break.";i:49;s:72:"When opening the door manually move it half way up and release the door.";i:50;s:87:"If the door stays where you release it the door springs are good and properly adjusted.";i:51;s:85:"If the door moves toward open or closed the door springs need adjusting or replacing.";i:52;s:90:"I recommend you get a garage door technician to correct any problem with the door springs.";i:53;s:54:"Open the garage door and watch it closely as it opens.";i:54;s:118:"When the garage door opens about halfway or 5 feet from the ground and stops the up limit switch needs to be adjusted.";i:55;s:50:"But occasionally the sensors can get out of whack.";i:56;s:75:"And one of the symptoms is a garage door that opens or closes only halfway.";i:57;s:32:"Sometimes the problem is simple.";i:58;s:31:"Something you can fix yourself.";i:59;s:70:"Here are three things to check before you call a service professional.";i:60;s:78:"Pull the emergency release cord to disengage the opener trolley from the door.";i:61;s:31:"Manually lift the door by hand.";i:62;s:148:"If the door opens without a hitch the fault lies with the automatic opener but if you can only open the door halfway the problem is the door itself.";i:63;s:111:"When the door is in any position other than closed and the garage door opener is activated the door will close.";i:64;s:144:"If the garage door makes contact with an obstruction while closing the door will reverse the opener will beep and the lights will flash 5 times.";i:65;s:146:"Garage door closes halfway then goes back up is important information accompanied by photo and HD pictures sourced from all websites in the world.";i:66;s:92:"Download this image for free in High-Definition resolution the choice download button below.";}}